<!channel> I've always chilled out in here personally and for the most part have not gotten involved in little arguments and such. Y'all typically do a good job of working it out and even up until have still done a decent job. However, recent "hot and heaviness" is starting to turn some people off-- me included. I really care about this group and you all have become an integral part of my magic life and life in general. I want it to continue to be healthy and inclusive.

We  strike a balance of being a casual group of friends and being a relatively large group of different personalities. I think this leads to us being more free to speak our minds in here, which is great. I want people to continue to do this and feel like this is a place where you can speak your mind, even if you are off base or just blowing off some steam. Let's just admit this is the nature of the beast and try to catch ourselves before it gets a bit too heavy. It's such a shame to hurt each other over relatively pretty stupid shit.

I want to try something out. It's something that works well for us at my day job's slack. I want sequester most ranting / bitching / shit talking to <#CHA8U3W1H|hot-and-heavy>. If you want to talk shit about someone on twitter, put it there. If you want to bitch about people bitching, put it there. If two of you get heated about some alt-right shit, move the conversation to there. What i've seen this do is the expectations of the channel are a little bit more lighthearted and it puts the conversation in a place where people know they are going to bitch about whatever and not take eachother very seriously. Also it takes the general negativity out of places like <#C8EPHVB40|spoilers> where we are suppose to be talking about new cards. What crosses the line between little jabs here in there in chat and something that needs to be quarantined can sometimes be gray. Everyone should help people realize this. When something hot and heavy comes up, take it upon yourself to say   "<#CHA8U3W1H|hot-and-heavy> --->"
